Complete Control Over Return Economics


Returns are an inevitable part of delivery operations and until now,
Return-to-Origin (RTO) costs couldn=E2=80=99t be modelled with the same pre=
cision
as forward deliveries.

With this release, network owners and managers can now *configure RTO
charges explicitly*, using the same flexible pricing framework already
available for delivery pricing.
Why We Built This

RTOs behave differently from forward deliveries. Costs may vary based on
distance, shipment characteristics, or commercial agreements and in many
cases, RTO charges are calculated as a percentage of the original delivery
price.

Previously, this logic couldn=E2=80=99t be represented cleanly within the p=
ricing
system, leading to manual adjustments or inconsistent handling of returns.

This update brings RTO pricing into the same structured, auditable system
as all other charges.
What=E2=80=99s New


RTO charges can now be configured just like standard pricing, using:

   -

   *Distance*
   -

   *Pincode*
   -

   *Unpaid Trips*
   -

   *Pricing Percentage*


All rules follow the same structure and behaviour as the existing pricing
module, ensuring familiarity and consistency.

Percentage-Based RTO Pricing

In addition to flat pricing, RTO charges now support a *Pricing Percentage*
 model.

When Pricing Percentage is selected:

   -

   The primary input is a *percentage value* (up to 2 decimal places)
   -

   The pricing structure mirrors the standard pricing rate card
   -

   All rates displayed reflect the *calculated value after applying the
   percentage*


This allows RTO charges to scale naturally with the original delivery
pricing, while still remaining fully visible and configurable.
What This Means For You

You can now define return charges with the same clarity and control as
forward pricing.

This means:

   -

   RTO costs are predictable and consistent
   -

   Return economics can be aligned with your commercial model
   -

   Manual calculations and post-facto adjustments are eliminated


Your pricing model now fully reflects the lifecycle of an order, including
returns.
What=E2=80=99s Next


We=E2=80=99re continuing to extend pricing intelligence across the full ord=
er
lifecycle, making every charge, adjustment, and exception configurable and
transparent.


More flexibility.
More precision.

Smarter enhancements ahead.
